  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Humanitarian Situation in Ghana and Cote D&apos;Ivoire Assessment for OI Positioning</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Situation in Cote d&apos;Ivoire (CdI) is evolving rapidly following the political unrest that started in November 2010, leading to huge human rights violations reported in Western CdI. The Humanitarian situation is reported to be considerably weak, and this is likely to continue deteriorating even if the Presidential question is resolved reasonably swiftly. There is limited response going on currently due to insecurity and uncertainly in the scope of the needs. This project is therefore aiming at assessing the humanitarian situation in Ghana and Cote d&apos;Ivoire in order to provide a clear picture for Oxfam positioning to emergency response.</narrative>
  </description>
